3ï¸âƒ£ Create MODEL Classes
ğŸ”¹ 3.1 Student Model

ğŸ“ Models â†’ Add â†’ Class â†’ Student.cs

using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace StudentResultMVC.Models
{
    public class Student
    {
        [Required]
        public int RollNo { get; set; }

        [Required]
        public string Name { get; set; }

        [Required]
        public string ContactNo { get; set; }
    }
}


ğŸ“Œ Purpose: Stores student details
ğŸ“Œ Required enables ModelState.IsValid

ğŸ”¹ 3.2 Marks Model

ğŸ“ Models â†’ Add â†’ Class â†’ Marks.cs

using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace StudentResultMVC.Models
{
    public class Marks
    {
        public int RollNo { get; set; }

        [Range(0, 100)]
        public int Sub1_Marks { get; set; }

        [Range(0, 100)]
        public int Sub2_Marks { get; set; }

        [Range(0, 100)]
        public int Sub3_Marks { get; set; }

        public int Total { get; set; }
        public double Percentage { get; set; }
        public string Result { get; set; }
    }
}

4ï¸âƒ£ Create VIEW MODEL (Combine Student + Marks)

ğŸ“ Models â†’ Add â†’ Class â†’ StudentResultVM.cs

namespace StudentResultMVC.Models
{
    public class StudentResultVM
    {
        public Student Student { get; set; }
        public Marks Marks { get; set; }
    }
}


ğŸ“Œ Why ViewModel?
To send multiple models to a single view.

5ï¸âƒ£ Create CONTROLLER

ğŸ“ Controllers â†’ HomeController.cs

using System.Web.Mvc;
using StudentResultMVC.Models;

namespace StudentResultMVC.Controllers
{
    public class HomeController : Controller
    {
        // GET: Input page
        public ActionResult Index()
        {
            return View();
        }

        // POST: Form submission
        [HttpPost]
        public ActionResult Index(StudentResultVM vm)
        {
            // Validation check
            if (!ModelState.IsValid)
            {
                return View(vm);
            }

            // Calculate total
            vm.Marks.Total =
                vm.Marks.Sub1_Marks +
                vm.Marks.Sub2_Marks +
                vm.Marks.Sub3_Marks;

            // Calculate percentage
            vm.Marks.Percentage = vm.Marks.Total / 3.0;

            // Pass/Fail logic
            if (vm.Marks.Sub1_Marks >= 35 &&
                vm.Marks.Sub2_Marks >= 35 &&
                vm.Marks.Sub3_Marks >= 35)
                vm.Marks.Result = "PASS";
            else
                vm.Marks.Result = "FAIL";

            // Redirect to result page
            return View("Result", vm);
        }
    }
}


ğŸ“Œ Controller flow:

User input â†’ Controller â†’ Model logic â†’ View

6ï¸âƒ£ Create VIEW â€“ Input Page

ğŸ“ Views â†’ Home â†’ Index.cshtml

@model StudentResultMVC.Models.StudentResultVM

<h2>Enter Student Result</h2>

@using (Html.BeginForm())
{
    <h3>Student Details</h3>

    <p>Roll No: @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.Student.RollNo)</p>
    <p>Name: @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.Student.Name)</p>
    <p>Contact No: @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.Student.ContactNo)</p>

    <h3>Marks</h3>

    <p>Subject 1: @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.Marks.Sub1_Marks)</p>
    <p>Subject 2: @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.Marks.Sub2_Marks)</p>
    <p>Subject 3: @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.Marks.Sub3_Marks)</p>

    <input type="submit" value="Calculate Result" />
}


ğŸ“Œ Html.BeginForm()

Creates <form>

Posts data to HomeController â†’ Index (POST)

7ï¸âƒ£ Create VIEW â€“ Result Page

ğŸ“ Views â†’ Home â†’ Result.cshtml

@model StudentResultMVC.Models.StudentResultVM

<h2>Student Result</h2>

<p>Roll No: @Model.Student.RollNo</p>
<p>Name: @Model.Student.Name</p>
<p>Contact: @Model.Student.ContactNo</p>

<p>Total Marks: @Model.Marks.Total</p>
<p>Percentage: @Model.Marks.Percentage</p>
<p>Result: <b>@Model.Marks.Result</b></p>

